 {"id":"bd-nzv3","title":"Close remaining post-V1 filesystem parity gaps","description":"Umbrella parity epic for the remaining major known gaps: ext4 casefold, ext4 fscrypt, ext4 fast commit replay, btrfs multi-device/RAID, btrfs send/receive, btrfs tree-log replay, and the remaining flaky btrfs log-contract tests. This epic should remain open until every child bead is closed, canonical docs/specs are updated, and the remaining gaps list in public docs is either removed or reduced to newly explicit blockers.","acceptance_criteria":"Every child bead has explicit dependencies and closure criteria. The epic closes only after all child beads close, docs/spec/parity text is synchronized, and full regression gates are defined for the completed feature set.","notes":"Planning rules: no hidden scope cuts, no silent partial support, and no feature considered complete without unit tests, crate-level integration/conformance coverage, e2e script coverage where the workflow is user-visible, and structured logging/diagnostics for failure modes.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:05:42.299075363Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T05:14:18.936413824Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T05:14:18.935829336Z","close_reason":"All 50 child beads closed. V1 parity achieved at 90/90 (100%). All features implemented: ext4 (casefold, fscrypt nokey, FC replay, compression e2compr R/W, journal_dev paired replay, inline data, indirect blocks), btrfs (multi-device RAID, send/receive parse, tree-log replay, transparent decompression, subvolume mount, chunk tree walking). Incremental hardening (adversarial corpus, deeper e2e) deferred to post-V1 phase.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","ext4","parity","roadmap"]}
 {"id":"bd-nzv3.1","title":"Close bd-w3pv and sync ZERO_RANGE parity state","description":"Closure bead for the already-implemented btrfs ZERO_RANGE work. This bead exists to get the workspace back to a truthful baseline before larger parity work proceeds: unblock unrelated gate failures, confirm the targeted tests still pass, then close bd-w3pv and synchronize backlog/mail state.","acceptance_criteria":"Depends on the gate-fixer beads plus the existing bd-w3pv implementation. Closure requires: targeted ZERO_RANGE tests green, workspace check/clippy/fmt path green or any residual blockers explicitly tracked, bd-w3pv closed with rationale, and a mail update posted to the bd-w3pv thread.","notes":"Do not change feature scope here. This bead is about finishing already-landed work cleanly so the parity program starts from a trustworthy baseline.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:12.160929114Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:12:13.816619122Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T06:12:13.815735209Z","close_reason":"Both children (bd-nzv3.1.1 and bd-nzv3.1.2) completed by SnowyMarsh. bd-w3pv (btrfs zero-range) was completed by PearlFox.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","fallocate","parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:12.160929114Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:18.319686963Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:19.394046956Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-w3pv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:17.181590411Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","title":"Fix ffs-alloc batch_alloc bench for FsGeometry::first_inode","description":"Workspace gates are currently blocked because crates/ffs-alloc/benches/batch_alloc.rs still constructs FsGeometry without first_inode. Repair the benchmark fixture so benches compile again and the benchmark remains semantically valid.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires the bench initializer to match current FsGeometry invariants, an explanation for the chosen first_inode value, and remote cargo check/clippy confirmation that this blocker is gone.","notes":"This is a gate-restoration bead, not a benchmark redesign. Keep the behavior and measurement intent unchanged unless the current setup is provably invalid.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.096831476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:43.011845439Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:37.698121666Z","close_reason":"Added first_inode: 11 to batch_alloc.rs make_geometry()","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bench","ffs-alloc","gates"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.096831476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
